00:00:06.480 --> 00:00:07.880
SHARI: Welcome to the
Smithsonian's

00:00:08.041 --> 00:00:09.350
National Museum of Natural History.

00:00:09.350 --> 00:00:11.561
SHARI: I'm Shari Werb, Director for
Education

00:00:11.723 --> 00:00:14.000
and Outreach. We've prepared this
short video

00:00:14.000 --> 00:00:15.928
to help you plan your visit.

00:00:15.928 --> 00:00:17.916
SHARI: Please check our
website to

00:00:18.078 --> 00:00:20.230
find information and field trip
resources

00:00:20.230 --> 00:00:23.276
to help you and your students make the
most

00:00:23.438 --> 00:00:26.948
out of your experience. When you
arrive, buses

00:00:26.948 --> 00:00:29.191
should drop off and pick up on the
Mall side

00:00:29.353 --> 00:00:31.650
of the Museum. Before your group gets
off

00:00:31.650 --> 00:00:33.863
the bus, please remind them that there
are

00:00:34.025 --> 00:00:36.400
no coat check facilities or lockers
here.

00:00:36.400 --> 00:00:38.396
Your students will need to leave their
lunches

00:00:38.558 --> 00:00:40.530
and any bags they don't want to carry,
on

00:00:40.530 --> 00:00:43.036
the bus. Food and drinks are not
allowed into

00:00:43.198 --> 00:00:45.750
the Museum and there are no provisions
for

00:00:45.750 --> 00:00:48.675
groups to store or eat bag lunches.
Discounted

00:00:48.836 --> 00:00:52.058
group meals in the Atrium Cafe may be
purchased

00:00:52.058 --> 00:00:54.683
before your visit by contacting
Smithsonian

00:00:54.845 --> 00:00:57.698
Group Sales. Groups not purchasing
food are

00:00:57.698 --> 00:00:59.440
welcome to picnic on the Mall.

00:00:59.440 --> 00:01:01.738
SECURITY OFFICER: Please open all
bags.

00:01:01.738 --> 00:01:04.580
SHARI: To speed entry into the
building,

00:01:04.741 --> 00:01:07.560
carry as little as possible. Security
checks

00:01:07.560 --> 00:01:10.108
are now required of Museum visitors,
and bags

00:01:10.270 --> 00:01:12.920
are thoroughly searched. When planning
your

00:01:12.920 --> 00:01:15.161
trip, keep in mind that you'll need to
arrange

00:01:15.323 --> 00:01:17.780
for one adult chaperone for every 10
students,

00:01:17.780 --> 00:01:20.996
grades 3 through 7 and one adult for
every

00:01:21.158 --> 00:01:24.780
15 students, grades 8 through 12. The
Museum

00:01:24.941 --> 00:01:27.638
offers educational materials to
visitors for

00:01:27.800 --> 00:01:30.820
use in the Museum, the classroom or
online.

00:01:30.820 --> 00:01:33.756
These can be printed before you
arrive. Teacher's

00:01:33.918 --> 00:01:36.640
Guides bring the expertise of our
research

00:01:36.640 --> 00:01:39.753
and collections to the classroom. All
of our

00:01:39.915 --> 00:01:43.640
programs and materials are free. You
may register

00:01:43.850 --> 00:01:46.678
online for our quarterly Educator E
newsletter.

00:01:46.840 --> 00:01:49.960
It includes information on educational
programs,

00:01:49.960 --> 00:01:52.685
exhibits, and special events. If
you're able

00:01:52.846 --> 00:01:55.670
to plan ahead, a variety of activities
can

00:01:55.670 --> 00:01:58.301
be booked by filling out exhibit
program request

00:01:58.463 --> 00:02:00.210
forms located on our website.

00:02:00.210 --> 00:02:03.671
DEMONSTRATOR: How does she eat? She
needs

00:02:03.833 --> 00:02:07.210
to put her fangs into it to paralyze
it.

00:02:07.310 --> 00:02:09.521
SHARI: Throughout the Museum
you will

00:02:09.683 --> 00:02:11.900
find volunteer interpreters. We
encourage

00:02:11.900 --> 00:02:14.071
students to ask them any questions
they might

00:02:14.233 --> 00:02:15.530
have about the exhibits.

00:02:15.530 --> 00:02:18.858
VOLUNTEER: And I'm going to pass
this group

00:02:19.020 --> 00:02:22.208
this one, I want you to figure out if
you

00:02:22.208 --> 00:02:24.766
think this belongs to a modern
Elephant or

00:02:24.928 --> 00:02:26.290
an ancient relative.

00:02:26.290 --> 00:02:28.670
SHARI: DISCOVER STATIONS are
positioned

00:02:28.831 --> 00:02:31.430
in selected exhibits. Groups of eight
to twelve

00:02:31.430 --> 00:02:34.691
visitors come face to face with object
based,

00:02:34.853 --> 00:02:38.430
problem solving opportunities and
experiences.

00:02:38.530 --> 00:02:41.488
Activities focus on exhibit concepts
and topics

00:02:41.650 --> 00:02:44.640
and take about five minutes to
complete. The

00:02:44.640 --> 00:02:46.733
Stations are generally available in
selected

00:02:46.895 --> 00:02:49.050
exhibits on Tuesdays through Fridays
from

00:02:49.050 --> 00:02:52.263
10:30 AM to noon. The DISCOVERY ROOM
is a

00:02:52.425 --> 00:02:56.050
hands on area featuring real Museum
objects

00:02:56.790 --> 00:03:00.005
and artifacts. Visitors can look at
fossils,

00:03:00.166 --> 00:03:03.700
skulls, shells and minerals, use a
microscope

00:03:03.700 --> 00:03:05.796
or try on costumes from around the
world.

00:03:05.958 --> 00:03:08.440
School groups should register online
to take

00:03:08.601 --> 00:03:09.943
advantage of morning programs during
the school

00:03:10.105 --> 00:03:10.606
year.

00:03:10.768 --> 00:03:12.760
[music]

00:03:12.760 --> 00:03:15.858
SHARI: Although your visit to
the

00:03:16.020 --> 00:03:19.760
Museum and activities are provided at
no cost,

00:03:20.870 --> 00:03:23.636
further experiences are available for
purchase.

00:03:23.798 --> 00:03:26.540
Standards connections are provided for
some

00:03:26.540 --> 00:03:29.073
of the educational films shown in the
Johnson

00:03:29.235 --> 00:03:31.930
IMAX Theater. BUTTERFLIES + PLANTS:
PARTNERS

00:03:31.930 --> 00:03:34.296
IN EVOLUTION is open to the public
free of

00:03:34.458 --> 00:03:37.048
charge. However, there is an entry fee
for

00:03:37.048 --> 00:03:39.531
admission to the Butterfly Pavilion at
all

00:03:39.693 --> 00:03:42.340
times except Tuesday. For additional
help

00:03:42.340 --> 00:03:45.946
in planning your visit, please call
our Education

00:03:46.108 --> 00:03:49.378
Office at, 202 633 1077. Before you
come,

00:03:51.278 --> 00:03:54.185
please check our website for the most
current

00:03:54.350 --> 00:03:57.010
information. We hope you and your
students

00:03:57.010 --> 00:04:00.090
enjoy your visit.

